## Additional Terms — Sonic-Forage

### Attribution Requirement

Any fork, derivative, or distribution of this software must:

1. **Retain the original copyright notice** and this license.
2. **Credit Sonic-Forage** in their README or documentation:
   > "Built on [Sonic-Forage](https://github.com/Sonic-Forage) — World's First Autonomous DJ Operating System"
3. **Link back** to the original repository: https://github.com/Sonic-Forage

### Share-Alike

If you modify or extend this software, you must:
1. Release your modifications under the same GPL v3 license.
2. Make your source code available to users.
3. Clearly mark what changes you made from the original.

### What You CAN Do

- ✅ Use it for personal projects
- ✅ Use it commercially (DJs, venues, festivals, labels)
- ✅ Modify it for your own needs
- ✅ Distribute it to others
- ✅ Build specialized workflows and sell support/services
- ✅ Create and sell premium content (templates, prompts, agents)
- ✅ Fork it and build your own ecosystem

### What You MUST Do

- ✅ Keep the license and copyright notice
- ✅ Credit Sonic-Forage in your project
- ✅ Open-source any modifications to the core code
- ✅ Use the same GPL v3 license for derivatives

### What You CANNOT Do

- ❌ Close-source the core code or your modifications
- ❌ Remove the attribution or license
- ❌ Claim you wrote the original code
- ❌ Sue the original authors (see Disclaimer below)

### Premium Content Exception

The following are NOT covered by GPL v3 and may be offered under separate terms:
- Specialized AI models and fine-tuned weights
- Premium ComfyUI workflows
- Custom agent configurations
- Training datasets
- Support and consulting services

These may be offered through Patreon, Buy Me a Coffee, or direct purchase.
The core code remains GPL v3 and always will.

